        <Parent_String>food storage structures [300005018], agricultural buildings [300004898], agricultural structures [300004895], single built works by function [300004894], single built works by specific type [300004795], single built works (built environment) [300004790], Single Built Works (hierarchy name) [300004789], Built Environment (hierarchy name) [300264550], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Structures for storing corn, usually with slotted boards for ventilation, slanted walls for weather protection, and set on stilts to deter rodents. For similar structures made of small-diameter, rough-hewn logs and used variously for food or equipment storage or animal shelter, use "crib barns."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Estructura para almacenar el maíz, generalmente con tablas abiertas para la ventilación o zacate entretejido, paredes sesgadas para protegerla del tiempo, y dispuesta sobre zancos para disuadir a los roedores. Para estructuras similares realizadas en pequeño diámetro, leños toscamente cortados y utilizadas variadamente para el almacenamiento de equipo o alimento, o como refugio animal se puede usar "crib barn".</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000121854/DEM, Diccionario del Español de México [online] (2025-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Gebouwen voor de opslag van maïs, meestal met spleten tussen de planken voor ventilatie, schuine muren voor bescherming tegen het weer en geplaatst op palen om knaagdieren weg te houden.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099099/Van Dale groot woordenboek (1994)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>用以貯存玉米的結構物，壁板通常留有縫隙，以便通風，壁面則傾斜以降低天氣的傷害，結構物底部並以樁柱架起，避免老鼠等齧齒類動物破壞。至於「秣料倉」一詞則指未經處理、尺寸較小之原木所建的類似結構物，泛用於貯存食物、設備或安置牲畜。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Bauwerk für die Lagerung von Mais, in der Regel mit geschlitzten Brettern zur Belüftung, geneigten Wänden zum Schutz vor Unwetter und auf Stelzen, um für Nagetiere nicht erreichbar zu sein. Eine ähnliche Vorrichtung aus grob gehauenen Holzstämmen mit geringem Durchmesser für die Lagerung von Nahrung, Utensilien oder auch als Schutz für Tiere wird als "Krippenscheune" bezeichnet.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Cinxahcalli campa quiahcocui cintli, tlachihualli ica huapalli tlapouhtoc tlen ica moehecahuiz, caltepamitl cahcactoc tlen quipalehuia queniuhqui tlaeltoc, huan hueli quinmahmatia quimichimeh. Quen quichiuhtoqueh cehca tlachihualli pan ce cuecuetztzin yahualtic, ica miac cuahuitl tlatectli huan motequihuia miac ica quiahcocuizceh tlen tlamantli zo tlacualiztli, zo quence campa motlatiz ce tlapiyalli zo tecuani, zo "crib barn".</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Eastern Huasteca Nahuatl</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
